text.text:
How can you reduce the chances of being ghosted while applying for a job on LinkedIn? An interesting question right? So let me help you out with a solution😉

While applying for jobs one big reason for not getting a reply is that a lot of candidates apply for the same job hence replying to everyone becomes tedious. So to receive a reply/test link is based on a factor called KISMAT.

And the following two steps will help you change it.

➡️Go to https://linkedin(dot)com/jobs 
➡️Search the following: Early Applicant AND Job Title

It helps you show all the jobs with the relevant job role where the competition (applicants) is less. Hence more chances of getting a callback. 

The screenshot in the media shows exactly the same.

Things to remember:
1. The query result largely depends on the availability of the jobs.
2. Relevance of results is considerably based on the number of openings following under the given category and location.

Hope it helps❤️

Share it with the ones in need. 
Follow Bhavishya Pandit for more insightful posts on Data Science, Python, Job search, Tricks and hacks in general!

#linkedin #india #jobalerts #job #career #datascience #python #jobsearch #openings #jobs

text.text:
Seriously I don't know will it be posted as achievement or not. But, after 16 months and experiencing backlog in two subjects, Finally I had completed the Foundation Cretificate course of the B.Sc in Programming and Data Science from IIT Madras. 
The journey of 16 months was like a roller coaster for me. I had come across a lot of ups and downs of life. Sometimes there is Happiness, sometimes there is Frustration. But despite of the challanges that I had come across, I enjoyed a lot.
This journey had taught me a serious lesson of Time Management, how to handle pressure when you are doing two degrees parallelly.
But what I loved the most was learning the subjects of Computational Thinking by Prof. Madhavan Mukund and G. Venkatesh, Programming in Python by Prof. Sudarshan Iyengar Iyenger and Mathematics by Prof. Neelesh Upadhye.
Once again, I would like to thank Indian Institute of Technology, Madras, IIT Madras Online Degree Programme for providing me this opportunity to experience World-Class education from my home.
